-- Indian shares edge higher on hopes of positive factory, inflation data 
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 06:10AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 12 (Reuters) - Indian shares edged higher on Thursday as blue-chips such as HDFC Bank <HDBK.NS> rose on hopes that economic data due later in the day may show easing retail inflation and a pick-up in industrial activity.

HDFC Bank provisionally rose 2.5 percent, while NTPC <NTPC.NS> advanced 1.9 percent.